.TH start-container-bind-mount 1  "bind-mount " 
.SH NAME
start\-container\-bind\-mount
.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBstart\-container bind\-mount\fR <\fB\-\-source\fR> <\fB\-\-target\fR> [\fB\-\-recursive\fR] [\fB\-\-readonly\fR] [\fB\-\-file\fR] [\fB\-\-idmap\fR] [\fB\-h\fR|\fB\-\-help\fR] 
.SH DESCRIPTION
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-\-source\fR \fI<SOURCE>\fR
Source path. May be any path on the filesystem; the kernel produces a detached bind clone via `open_tree(OPEN_TREE_CLONE)`
.TP
\fB\-\-target\fR \fI<TARGET>\fR
Mountpoint to attach to. Created if it doesn\*(Aqt exist (as a directory, unless `\-\-file` is set)
.TP
\fB\-\-recursive\fR
Apply the bind recursively (the `\-\-rbind` semantic)
.TP
\fB\-\-readonly\fR
Mark the mount read\-only via `mount_setattr(MOUNT_ATTR_RDONLY)`
.TP
\fB\-\-file\fR
Treat the target as a regular file rather than a directory when creating it
.TP
\fB\-\-idmap\fR \fI<IDMAP>\fR
Idmap entries; repeat the flag for each entry. Format `from:to[:range]` (range defaults to 1)
.TP
\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR
Print help
